@NODE introduction "Introduction"
@NEXT copyright
@PREV main

   First, there are a lot of different drive speed test programmes.
   But none of them has the features we want to have.
   So we decided to write an own program that includes these features
   which are:
      @{i}
      test of several devices at the same time,
      graphical display at runtime,
      that you can change buffersize and testmode while the test
      and that you can add/remove devices to/from a running test.
      @{ui}
   So, this is a short overview of the present features.
   Now test it and @{"write us" link authors} your opinion and/or suggestions.

   For futher releases it's planned to include more testmodes and
   more graphical displays.

@ENDNODE

